  "text": "IGlarLixi is a fixed-ratio combination of insulin glargine and lixisenatide, containing 100 U/mL of glargine and 33 lg/mL of lixisenatide in a 3-mL prefilled injection pen. Glargine U100 is a basal insulin with postinjection precipitation that achieves a protracted action (T1/2 = 12.5 h) [CITATION_1] . Lixisenatide is an exendin-derived GLP-1RA for which PPG lowering is brought about mostly through delayed gastric emptying and reduced glucagon release. Lixisenatide has a half-life of only 2-4 h. This relatively shorter half-life means that PPG control occurs mainly in the meal after injection [CITATION_2] .",
